(define/contract (min-operations nums k)
  (-> (listof exact-integer?) exact-integer? exact-integer?)
  (let loop ((nums (reverse nums)) ; Reverse the list to start from the end
             (collected (make-hash)) ; Use a hash to track collected elements
             (ops 0)) ; Operations counter
    (cond
      [(= (hash-count collected) k) ops] ; If we've collected all elements, return ops
      [else
       (let ((last (car nums))) ; Get the last element of the original array
         (hash-set! collected last #t) ; Mark this element as collected
         (loop (cdr nums) collected (+ ops 1)))]))) ; Continue with the rest
